<p>Here's a simple type hierarchy.</p>  <pre><code>type Parent() = class end type Child() = inherit Parent() </code></pre>  <p>I want to treat a function of type <code>('x -&gt; Child)</code> as <code>('x -&gt; Parent)</code>:</p>  <pre><code>let f (x: 'x): Child = new Child() let g: ('x -&gt; Parent) = f // error </code></pre>  <p>But that last assignment fails, with the message <code>The type 'Parent' does not match the type 'Child'</code>. Is there a way to make this work?</p>